ALPINE SKIING - PROFILE OF WOMEN ' S SUPER - G WINNER . Profile of the winner of a women ' s World Cup super - G on Saturday : Name : Isolde KostnerAge : 21Nation : ItalyPrevious World Cup wins : 3 downhills - Garmisch 1994 , Cortina 1996 , Cortina 1997Other facts : Double Olympic bronze medallist in 1994 and reigning super - G world champion . Her first win at Garmisch was overshadowed by tragedy when Austria ' s Ulrike Maier died in a crash on the course . Her father is a traditional woodcarver in Val Gardena and Kostner sometimes helps him to paint the statues he makes . Has now won three of her four victories in Cortina . 
